The paper deals with object recognition using Convolutional Neural Networks (ConvNets) and memory-based frameworks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine-labeled image annotations, which is a topic related to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) controllers and attention mechanisms, which are techniques commonly used in Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.IR.
